      "updated": "Tue, 23 Aug 2011 21:00:00 EST", 
      "author": "Mike Schramm", 
      "title": "McAfee: Android malware soars while iPhone untouched", 
      "cover": "-", 
      "summary": "<!--CONTENT START--><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"295\" src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com//media/2011/08/androidlogo.jpg\" style=\"float: right; margin: 0 0 8px 8px; border: none;\" width=\"250\" />\n<p>\n\tMcAfee says that the Android OS is having some issues with malware lately -- according to <a href=\"http://www.electronista.com/articles/11/08/23/mcafee.shows.android.facing.huge.spike.in.malware/\">a new study from the anti-malware company</a>, Android malware has grown by 76% over the past few months, sending the number of troublesome scripts out there to over 40. Some of the malware appears to be legitimate apps, and other issues  come from code that sends unwanted text messages or performs other scammy behavior.</p>\n<p>\n\tMeanwhile, Apple is doing great with iOS -- McAfee has recorded zero legitimate threats to a stock iPhone, with the only attacks on the hardware coming to four different jailbroken devices. It appears Apple's \"walled garden\" approach, while limiting to some developers and customers, has at least made good use of those walls in  keeping malware away.</p>\n<p>\n\tThe other mobile OS with a spotless score? webOS, which of course is probably that way simply because it's just not used that much.</p><p style=\"padding: 5px; clear: both;\"><a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2011/08/23/mcafee-android-malware-soars-while-iphone-untouched/\">McAfee: Android malware soars while iPhone untouched</a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com\">TUAW - The Unofficial Apple Weblog</a> on Tue, 23 Aug 2011 21:00:00 EST.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds</a>.<br style=\"clear: both;\" /></p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://www.electronista.com/articles/11/08/23/mcafee.shows.android.facing.huge.spike.in.malware/\">Source</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2011/08/23/mcafee-android-malware-soars-while-iphone-untouched/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/forward/20024945/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">Email this</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2011/08/23/mcafee-android-malware-soars-while-iphone-untouched/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">Comments</a>", 
      "feeds": [
        "latest"
      ], 
      "guid": "http://www.tuaw.com/2011/08/23/mcafee-android-malware-soars-while-iphone-untouched/"
